
---


@startuml

' Define classes with attributes and associations
class Company {
  +name: String
}

class BusLine {
  +lineNumber: Integer
  +category: String
}

class Trajectory {
  +id: String
  +approvalStatus: ApprovalStatus
  +startDate: Date
  +endDate: Date (nullable)
}

enum ApprovalStatus {
  Pending
  Approved
  Rejected
  Revised
}

class Bus {
  +busId: String
  +assignedTrajectory: Trajectory
}

class MENSO {
  +customerId: String
  +personalData: Map<String, String>
  +trips: List<Trip>
  +invoiceHistory: List<Invoice>
}

class Trip {
  +tripId: String
  +date: Date
  +time: Time
  +line: BusLine
}

class Invoice {
  +invoiceId: String
  +month: MonthYear
  +amount: Decimal
  +discount: Decimal
  +paid: Boolean
}

class Payment {
  +paymentId: String
  +invoice: Invoice
  +amountPaid: Decimal
  +paymentDate: Date
}

class MonthYear {
  +year: Integer
  +month: Integer
}

class Customer {
  +customerId: String
  +menso: MENSO
  +homeAddress: String
  +officeAddress: String
  +workingHours: List<TimeRange>
}

class TimeRange {
  +startTime: Time
  +endTime: Time
}

' Associations and Relationships
Company "1" -- "many" BusLine : owns
Company "1" -- "many" Trajectory : manages
Company "1" -- "many" Bus : owns
BusLine "1" *-- "many" Trajectory : contains
Trajectory "0..*" -- "1" Bus : assigned to
Trajectory "1" -- "many" Trip : includes
MENSO "1" -- "many" Trip : records
Customer "1" -- "1" MENSO : subscribes to
Trip "1" -- "1" BusLine : belongs to
Invoice "1" -- "1" MENSO : generated for
Payment "1" -- "1" Invoice : pays for
MENSO "1" -- "many" Invoice : has
MENSO "1" -- "many" Payment : receives

@enduml

---

### 🔍 Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Company**: Central entity that owns buses, manages trajectories, and operates bus lines.
- **BusLine**: A route identified by a line number. May consist of multiple overlapping or variant trajectories.
- **Trajectory**: A specific path that must be approved by town authorities before it can be operational.
- **ApprovalStatus**: Enum representing the status of trajectory approval.
- **Bus**: Each bus can be assigned to one trajectory at a time.
- **MENSO**: User subscription system; tracks trips, invoices, discounts, and customer data.
- **Trip**: Records each ride made with a MENSO card, including date, time, and line.
- **Invoice & Payment**: Handles billing logic—invoices may come in any order relative to payments.
- **Customer**: Stores personal information used for behavioral analysis.
- **MonthYear**: Utility class for grouping trips into monthly billing cycles.
- **TimeRange**: Used to represent working hours for behavioral insights.

---

### 📌 Notes:
- This model supports the iterative approval process for trajectories.
- It allows for flexible assignment of buses to trajectories once they are approved.
- The `MENSO` class encapsulates all trip data needed for invoicing and discount calculation.
- The system supports delayed payment scenarios as per the requirement.

